    "caption": "Fuzzy, loud, and built for cold weather.",
    "shortDescription": "Bumblebees are chubbier and fuzzier than honeybees, and they can fly in cold, wet weather that would ground other bees. They buzz-pollinate flowers by vibrating their flight muscles so fast the pollen shakes loose — that vibration is what you feel if a bumblebee lands on your hand. Fun fact: Bumblebee queens hibernate alone underground all winter, then start a whole new colony by themselves in spring."
